event-handlers are programs installed in $PATH, that are executed (triggered)
by external programs in response to various events.

class			- called by standalone bash scripts via `. class'.
init-event		- called by init, as per inittab.
mysql-backup-event	- called by myisam backup tasks.
pam-event		- called by PAM on login, etc.
udev-event		- called by udev for new devices, etc.
